Subject Re IBMPC XT switch settings

In article 1qk158kcpbigbirdhricom obrienbigbirdhricom writes
I just got an IBMPC XT with no documents Its a true
IBM and I was wondering if anyone had the definitions
of the 2 8 position dip switches 

SW8SW7	number of 525 drives
00	1 drive
01	2 drives
10	3 drives
11	4 drives

SW6SW5	type of display
00	reserved
01	40x25 color mono mode
10	80x25 color mono mode
11	mono 80x25

SW4SW3	amount of memory on system board
	64k chips	256k chips
00	64k		256k
01	128k		512k
10	192k		576k
11	256k		640k

SW2	coprocessor installed
SW1	loop on POST
